LongDescription: Small and fast, designed to transport passengers between nearby stations in orbit.  They can't travel far, but they can certainly get somewhere in a hurry.
FlavorText:
Vance,

I assume you're familiar with the manufacturer known as Montague? Syd Montague- their chairman- has decided to join the cause for the OSP and we've managed to broker a deal to provide discrete access to the Eight Ball Belt in return for their professional engineering. Weaponry, delicate parts, mostly support equipment, all things that will help us immensely. However, the real boon is that Montague is giving us their fleet of Ferryman-class shuttles.

I'm authorizing you to take a number of them from Pyxis and arm them how you see fit. Make no mistake- these are incredibly speedy vessels but they're designed to haul passengers (and marines) and even with Command Engineering's refits, you won't be able to mount heavy weapons. My technicians tell me that these aren't exactly luxury shuttles, so if you're looking for seat warmers, you'll be disappointed but that just means it'll keep you nice and awake, yes?

- Constantine
